HOUSING ACT 1988
The Housing Act 1988 is an Act of Parliament in the United Kingdom .
It governs the law between landlords and tenants .
The Act introduced the concepts of assured tenancy and assured shorthold tenancy .
It also facilitated the transfer of council housing to not - for - profit housing associations .
